Package io.honeycomb.libhoney

Interface EventPostProcessor


  • public interface EventPostProcessor
    Applies post-processing to events being submitted to Honeycomb. This occurs only for events that have been sampled, and just after the event's dynamic fields have been resolved. The EventData being passed to the post processor can be safely mutated, but must subsequently still pass validation. See HoneyClient's class documentation for the "Event Validation" rules.

    Post-processing occurs on the thread that invokes any of the send*() methods.

    Any exceptions occuring will stop the event from being sent and reported back as a ClientRejected response.
